of course the World Cup win. They have become a Soccer obsessed nation with a new-found national passion and 1 million people came together on the streets and celebrated for one whole week!

Uruguay is like the black sheep of South America with a population of things to see and do and enjoy, but once you step out of the capital the numbers quickly die down. Montevideo is where local Spring Break is at, Plaza De Toross where locals row on the water is always buzzing with young people on the weekends, Birth of new buildings and cutting edge Art and Design studios make it interesting.

When you find yourself in Rio, do not go to Uruguay yet. Do all your driving south, go visit the hidden gem that is Patagonia, breath the crisp nature air of the Pampas and then the next day step foot foot into Montevideo and be surprised. It’s better than you think.
